      <methods>
         <methodStep>
            <description>
               <section>
                  <para>Photosynthetically active radiation (PAR) is measured using LI190SB LI-COR quantum radiation sensors. A total of five below-canopy sensors measure downwelling PAR below the forest canopy.  The sensors are mounted on posts approximately 0.5 meters above the ground surface and are located roughly 20-m from the walk-up tower at equidistant spacing. Above-canopy quantum sensors (upwelling and downwelling) are mounted on a boom extended from the tower at a height of 23-m. Downwelling and upwelling solar radiation measurements are recorded using a Kipp and Zonen thermopile pyranometer, and global (total) and diffuse PAR measurements are measured using a BF3 sunshine sensor (both at 23-m). BF3 sensor photodiodes are cosine corrected and calibrated for the measurement of PAR quanta. Soil temperatures at 20-cm depth are measured with Campbell Scientific 107-L probes in four locations distributed around the walk-up tower and co-located with PAR sensors. Air temperatures are measured using a shaded CS107-L probe at 23-m.</para>
               </section>
            </description>
         </methodStep>
      </methods>
